nd, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Ravenel","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: habitational name from Ravenel, the name of several places in various parts of France, e.g. in Oise, derived from Old French <i>ravene</i> (from Latin <i>raphanus</i>) ‘horseradish’.","History: This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of South Carolina."],"variants":[{"name":"Ravenelle","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Gaetan, Normand, Raoul.","French: variant of   Ravenel   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","History: Christophe Ravenelle <i>dit</i> Lalime, a French soldier from Nancy, Lorraine, who married Agathe Charron in QC in 1758, was born <i>Ravenel</i>. Some of his descendants bear the surname   Lalime  ."]},{"name":"Ravenell","meanings":["Altered form of French   Ravenel  .","Possibly also a rare variant of English   Ravenhill   or its cognates <b>Ravenhall</b> or <b>Revnell</b>."]}]},{"name":"Mathilde","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."],"variants":[{"name":"Mechtild","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."]},{"name":"Matilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]},{"name":"Mechtilde","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mathilde de Ravenel was born in 1154, in France as the daughter of Dame Des Biards. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with William Vernon , Baron of Nehou."},"et":{"1154–":"1154–Surnud","1154–Female":"1154–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1153–1195":"1153–1195","1148–1214":"1148–1214","1190–1234":"1190–1234","1179–Male":"1179–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1190":"1190","1214":"1214","1148":"1148","1179":"1179","1234":"1234","1154":"1154","1153":"1153","1195":"1195","Shipbrook, Chester, England":"Shipbrook, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Exeter, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1154–":"1154–Kuollut","1154–Female":"1154–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1153–1195":"1153–1195","1148–1214":"1148–1214","1190–1234":"1190–1234","1179–Male":"1179–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1190":"1190","1214":"1214","1148":"1148","1179":"1179","1234":"1234","1154":"1154","1153":"1153","1195":"1195","Shipbrook, Chester, England":"Shipbrook, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Exeter, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1154–":"1154–Décédée","1154–Female":"1154–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1153–1195":"1153–1195","1148–1214":"1148–1214","1190–1234":"1190–1234","1179–Male":"1179–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1190":"1190","1214":"1214","1148":"1148","1179":"1179","1234":"1234","1154":"1154","1153":"1153","1195":"1195","Shipbrook, Chester, England":"Shipbrook, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Exeter, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Mathilde de Ravenel est née en 1154, à France,